README for jlib-1.2.x
------------------------
jlib is a library of STL compatible C++ utility classes.


REQUIREMENTS
------------
1. gcc-3.1         <http://gcc.gnu.org>
2. libsigc++-1.0.3 <http://libsigc.sourceforge.net>
3. openssl         <http://www.openssl.org>

INSTALLATION
------------
First, make sure you're using gcc-3.0 or greater.  No gcc-2.x compiler
will work, since the STL support is extremely primitive.  I've never
tried compiling with a non-gcc compiler; if you get it to work, send me
a note.

If you're installing from CVS, you first need to 

    libtoolize && aclocal && autoheader && automake -a && autoconf

For the default installation:

	./configure
	make
	make install


If you want to change any of the defaults, 

	./configure --with-OPTION=VALUE

For a list of options,
	
	./configure --help

